Job Details
Project Engineering.Perform Feasibility Study.
Prepare complete tender document.
Develop Scope of Work.
Perform structural analysis and design for reinforced concrete structures.
Perform structural analysis and design of steel structures.
Have worked in designing / construction of prefabricated building.Design and detail reinforced concrete and steel structures.
Design and detail welded and bolted connections.Design and detail reinforced concrete foundations for storage tanks and for rotary equipment to sustain static and dynamic loads as applicable.
Perform and review Concrete Mix Design.Shall review and comment on “EPC" project.
Evaluate existing structures for additional loads / design modiﬁcationsFamiliar with International Standards and Codes such as: ACI, UBC, AISC, AWS,ASTM, AASHTO, BS, DIN and API.Q
Can perform structural analysis using Software programs such as STAAD Pro. or other well-known structural software programs.
Familiar with Microsoft Ofﬁce.Prepare repair procedure and sketches for deteriorated reinforced concrete and steel structures.
Familiarity with AutocadGood knowledge of building materials.
Requirements
Relevant Degree in Civil Engineering
Oil field experience is a must
Minimum 5 years of experience in Design, Construction and Project Engineering for Oil and Gas Projects
Can speak and write English ﬂuently
